  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Instead, most predictions are moderately influenced by multiple training instances working in concert (Feldman & Zhang, 2020; Das et al., 2021; Basu et al., 2020).",
    "As an additional complicating factor, pointwise influence within data-distribution modes is often approximately supermodular where the marginal effect of a training instance's deletion increases as more instances from a group are removed (Hammoudeh & Lowd, 2022).",
    "This makes pointwise influence a particularly poor choice for understanding most model behavior.",
    "To date, very limited work has systematically studied group influence (Koh et al., 2019; Basu et al., 2020; Hammoudeh & Lowd, 2022).",
    "Better group influence estimators could be immediately applied in various domains such as poisoning attacks, coreset selection, and model explainability."
  ],
